<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 20th year of Rājarājatēvar. To Mahādeva of Tiruvālantuṟai of this Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, the wife/queen <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tēviyār</foreign></supplied> of Vaṉānuṭeyār, Naṭṭaṉ <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāṭṭaṉ</foreign> &gt; <foreign>naṭṭaṉ</foreign>?, the dancer</supplied> Ceyaḷ Naṅkai, gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vacca</foreign></supplied> a perpetual <supplied reason="lost">lamp</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p></div>

